<h2>We are seeking Founding Members for our new YourOnlineMom Board of Advisors</h2>
<div class="row" style="background-color: #E0D2C3; padding-top: 15px; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px">
  <h3 class="aboutHeader">Mission: Create a culture where we can have conversations that help us grow intellectually and protect each other from harassment</h3>
      <h4><br>
        ThinQ.tv is seeking a Founding Board of Advisors.  <br><br>
      </h4>
</div>  

<div class="row" style="background-color: #F2EBE4" >
      <h3 style = "color:#8C1D40">Required Qualifications: </h3>
      <div style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5em">
        - Experience in planning and implementing advocacy strategies and campaigns to support an issue or cause. <br> 
        - Connected leader in tech or women's communities who can leverage networks and resources in support of efforts to positively impact the live video tech culture. <br>
        - Significant presence in social media, as evidenced by having written well-researched content. <br>
      </div> 

      <h3 style = "color:#8C1D40">Purpose of the YourOnlineMom Board of Advisors: </h3>
      <div style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5em">
        Carry out the mission of YourOnlineMom by:<br>
        - Attend virtual Board meetings and host <%= link_to "Online Mom", parents_path %> sessions<br>
        - Advocate for what we're doing to combat online sexual harassment via your articles, speaking, social media<br>
        - Nominate other responsible adults to become Online Parents and Siblings<br>
        - Participate in developing and refining the <%= link_to 'Bystander Guidelines', bystanderguidelines_path %> for addressing online harassment
        - Fundraising <br>
      </div> 

      <h3 style = "color:#8C1D40">How to Apply to be on the Board of Directors: </h3>
      <div style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5em">
        - Drop in to any of the YourOnlineMom Conversations by Dr. Lisa Schaefer listed on the <%= link_to 'ThinQ.tv schedule', "/" %> so we can meet you <br>
        - Send resume and cover letter to info@ThinQ.tv. Cover letter must describe your goals or mission for participating on the Board. <br>
      </div> 
